category comment: 

clue: You don't have to be a Marvel hero to have this awareness of danger introduced in a 1962 comic book

response: Spider-sense

clue: 18th century essayist Richard Steele coined this phrase for a payment made to get someone to keep quiet

response: hush money

clue: Jane Austen wrote in a letter, "It was 12 before we reached home. We were all" this hyphenated canine phrase

response: dog-tired

clue: The practice of putting ailing seamen below decks is a possible origin of this phrase meaning not feeling too good

response: under the weather

clue: A James Thurber character who's full of expressions not only uses "the catbird seat" but "tearing up" this garden area

response: the pea patch

